name: Bikini Bottom
description:
In Filip Hodas’s Bikini Bottom, the
iconic and beloved cartoon
character SpongeBob is
represented as a washed-up relic
under a bridge at an empty canal,
sitting there alone, left as rusty
and old, exuding an underlying
melancholy that children would be
oblivious to. SpongeBob’s jolly
face and happy expression betray
the dire situation, juxtaposing
emotions that Hodas compares to
the parable of the American
movie star
